data.text:
This page contains audio recordings from over 15 years-worth of DXing. Browse the list below to hear how radio stations sounded when logged in Woodbridge, VA, often hundreds of thousands of miles away from the stations transmitter. To listen to a recording, click on the   icon to the left of the stations call letters. Depending on your browser, it will either automaticallly play the file in a new tab, or it will download the file.

This page is updated regularly throughout the year as I receive new DX. Click here to see posts with new audio added by date.

PLEASE NOTE: All recordings presented on this page were recorded over-the-air from publically-broadcasted radio transmissions. These recordings are copyrighted materials and are presented on this page solely for educational, critical commentary, and identification purposes only, and are thus believed to qualify as fair use under United States copyright law. With this said, this website will fully comply with takedown/removal requests from authorized copyright holders. Please read this websites full copyright disclaimer for more details and to request a takedown/removal.

Click on a link below to jump to that specific state, or scroll down to view all recordings.
